CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 13, 1957, pg. A1, reads: "Area Scouts Leave for Jamboree - These young fellows are just a small number of the Allegheny Council Boy Scouts who left Pittsburgh earlier this week to attend this  year's National Boy Scout Jamboree at Valley Forge, Pa. Included in the jamboree program was a sightseeing trip to Washington, D. C.  - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Boy Scouts wearing uniforms and holding cameras, posed with camping gear and duffel bags, on way to National Boy Scout Jamboree
